  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function unichar_ismark(c: String): Boolean {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_unichar_ismark()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Determines whether a character is a mark (non-spacing mark,
combining mark, or enclosing mark in Unicode speak).
Given some UTF-8 text, obtain a character value
with <link xref="GLib.utf8_get_char"/>.</p>  <p>Note: in most cases where isalpha characters are allowed,
ismark characters should be allowed to as they are essential
for writing most European languages as well as many non-Latin
scripts.</p>
  <p>Since 2.14</p>
